Description: hamstr implements a "Bacon-like" Bayesian sediment accumulation or age-depth model with hierarchically structured multi-resolution discrete sediment sections. The Bayesian model is implemented in the Stan probabilistic programming language (https://mc-stan.org/). "Blaauw, Maarten, and J. AndrÃ©s Christen. 2011. 'Flexible Paleoclimate   Age-Depth Models Using an Autoregressive Gamma Process.'  Bayesian Analysis 6 (3): 457-74. doi:10.1214/ba/1339616472"
